2 Params

# memory exhaustion if I try to make all of these large 
# for checking the distributions - need to increased the numbers here
k <- 50 #schools
j <- 8  # teachers 
i <- 20 # students

icc3 <- 0.05  # icc for school 
icc2 <- 0.20 # icc for teachers
R2 <- .40


ps_coef <- matrix(c(-1.25, 1, .25, 1.5, 1.5, .20, .20))  #what values for pi 6 and 7 in the notes?
pr_star <- .5

outcome_coef <- matrix(c(1, 0.3, 0.1, 0.1, 0.5, 0.4, 0.1, 0.1, -0.2, 1, 1))

delta <- -0.4

3 Generate Data

set.seed(20210527)

example_dat <- generate_data(k = k,
                             j = j, 
                             i = i, 
                             icc3 = icc3, 
                             icc2 = icc2, 
                             R2 = R2,
                             ps_coef = ps_coef, 
                             pr_star = pr_star, 
                             outcome_coef = outcome_coef, 
                             delta = delta)

4.5 Check Model Params

4.5.1 Coefficients

out_mod <- lmer(Y_ijk ~ D  + X_ijk + W_jk + Z_k + 
                    (1 | school_id/teacher_id),
                  data = example_dat)
